result.execSummary:
The defendant Roneshia L North was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Roneshia L North is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Roneshia L North was found guilty of 2nd-Degree Recklessly Endangering Safety [Modifiers: As a Party to a Crime], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.30(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: If probation or extended supervision is revoked or will discharge with outstanding financial obligations due, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due.

Defendant shall not enter any establishment where the primary purpose is the sale or service of alcohol.
Defendant shall not have direct or indirect contact with Darryl or Christine S. or their children or residences. 
Defendant shall not have direct of indirect contact with Marcelleous H.

Defendant shall participate in an AODA assessment and a mental health evaluation and all counseling or treatment programs as directed by her supervising agent. 
Defendant shall provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis.  Defendant has the right to request expungement of DNA analysis in writing through the Department of Justice.
Defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety.
